reviews_data.review_text:
Muddled Mint Cold Brew…that’s why. That and so many more reasons. Their branded coffee canteens come with built in tea strainers. Sara made me an excellent Sea Salt Caramel Oat Milk Latte but then she and I got to talking and I did something I never do, ordered a second coffee just to try it. Come in ready for that type of experience!

They work with Crown Town compost, who picks up their waste weekly. Sara tells me that coffee shops can compost virtually everything, which was great to learn. They are eco friendly and offer a host of alternative milks. Their beans are locally roasted and the pastries are baked in Charlotte as well.

They have two locations in Charlotte and I’m sorry to only be able to visit one. Next visit it will be on my list.

reviews_data.review_text: Exceptional pour over in Uptown, Charlotte.  It was flavorful and bold, without leaving me jittery.  The owner, Chris, was great to talk to and excitedly shared his brewing techniques.  He is also very sustainable-minded.  Highly recommend.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey Michael, it was great chatting with you and your wife! Thanks for stopping by.

reviews_data.review_text: Great service, great coffee, great food. I love the fact the Crane thinks about the environment with their coffee cups and lids and that they use local chefs and bakers for their food choices.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your kind words Thomas, and for taking the time to leave us a review. We are so happy you enjoyed coming in. Look forward to seeing you next time you are in Charlotte!

reviews_data.review_text: Cute little  coffee shop! It’s run by a super friendly couple and the drinks are great
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for stopping in Lisa, and for taking the time to leave us a review! We are so glad you enjoyed your drinks and appreciate your kind words.🌺

reviews_data.review_text: Spent 6 days in Uptown Charlotte from New York. Found Crane by accident on Day 1. My wife and I went back every morning while we were in town..My best cup of coffee ☕ in my 65 yrs of living. Chris is a great host.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the kind words Jack. You and Michelle were a pleasure to get to know

reviews_data.review_text: Best coffee in Charlotte, hands down!  Love the Bullet Proof or the Muddled Mint Iced Coffee.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Jeremy, thank you for leaving a review! Delighted to hear your feedback on the coffees, glad you enjoy them!

reviews_data.review_text: Best coffee in the city, hands down. Amazing specialty brews. Pour-over method. Friendly service. Absolutely worth the short walk to NASCAR Plaza if you're uptown.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Peter, we appreciate your review very much, thank you!!

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee, breakfast sandwiches and service! Stop by crane and check it out.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Adam, thank you very much for your review!  Our apologies for the delay in thanking you, we missed your review somehow.. We are so glad you enjoy stopping into the shop!

reviews_data.review_text:
I asked if the coffee was good, and he said it was the best in town

He was telling the truth! Amazing coffee.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Andrew, thank you kindly for your review. We are so happy that you enjoyed our coffee!

reviews_data.review_text:
Best coffee in Uptown! All coffee is pour over and prices are very reasonable.

A highly recommend in my book! Even though this location is further from my office than other coffee shops, I'll make the extra effort to come by!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much Paul, appreciate the kind words. Glad you enjoy our coffee!

reviews_data.review_text: I'd give him zero stars for closing when he said he was going to go mobile. Such a great idea. Bummer outcome.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Dear Fartart Tart,
I understand your disappointment and appreciate that you are a fan of our coffee. Due to unforseen familial circumstances with the outbreak of Covid-19 I, Kris the owner and sole operator, was forced to postpone operations. This was indeed a bummer outcome. We look forward to being up and runing in 2021 whether it be at our Uptown location, a mobile unit, or a new space entirely. Hope you and your loved ones are doing well.

Peace and Love,
Kris

reviews_data.review_text: One of the best cups of French Roast I've ever had.
Best pour over coffee in uptown with great friendly service.
Great coffee! Small place but the service is always quick and professional. I always stop and grab a pour ever whenever I'm in town for work. Highly suggest anyone trying out Crane Coffee Company!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your kind words, Andrew!

reviews_data.review_text: Very nice place...coffee was made to order and fresh cream was nice...
Chris is amazing and the coffee was delicious! So glad we stopped while we were in town.
I love this place! The mint iced coffee is so delicious and the atmosphere is very relaxing. I love all the natural light and artwork.
Great coffee! Small place, but I love the very different, hard to find, coffee drinks they offer. Prices are average coffee shop prices.

A great spot for pour over coffee. There is a few seats for those who chose to enjoy their coffee in the comfort of the AC and several pieces of art, or enjoy a seating outside watching the "coming and going".

Really great service!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Mel, thank you kindly for your review. We are so happy that you enjoyed your experience at the shop!!

reviews_data.review_text: Love this place!
Incredible pour over coffee. Best cup in town.

First experience this morning and it looks like a winner. I tried one of their handcrafted spiced drinks which was probably the best I've had in a while. Will definitely be back. Patrons should be aware that "handcrafted" does take time. Similar to a pour over, but worth the wait.
Great service and great coffee. I highly recommend this place to anyone looking for fantastic tasting coffee. The food was also homemade and equally fantastic.

You won't find any coffee shop like this in uptown Charlotte. They've got delicious one-of-a-kind specialty drinks here, personable service, and a cozy environment. Even if you are a far walk away, it's totally worth it. Only wish they would be open more hours.
reviews_data.owner_answer: James, sorry for the late reply here to you! But wanted to say thank you for your review. We appreciate you taking the time!

reviews_data.review_text: Great little coffee joint with terrific pour over. Service is a little slow but that is to be expected for a handcrafted cup of joe. Not the ambiance of Coca and the Director but it’s a small space. Looking forward to going back soon!
